						<div class="postbody">If your memory is twice as fast as the CPU, I don't see how hard it would be to work DRAM into your design. The Apple II multiplexed CPU, video, and refresh with just discrete logic. On the Super NES, memory would need to be capable of 7.2 MHz operation for this to work in fast ROM mode.</div>

